propel their candidate to the lead in the close race.
   Unlike the first presidential debate on Sept. 25, when
candidates and aides tried to set low expectations, Dukakis was
predicting a win.
   ``We're ahead 2-0 and we're going to make it a clean sweep,''
Dukakis said, referring to his debate with Bush and Bentsen's
confrontation with Quayle.
