where I'd like to see us be in the '90s if I'm elected president.''
   Bush then headed off to Dodger Stadium where he watched the Los
Angeles Dodgers defeat the New York Mets 6-0 to capture the
National League pennant and win a spot in baseball's World Series.
   ``Great night. I'll tell you, once in awhile you luck into
something really fun,'' Bush told reporters who accompanied him to
the game. ``Can't say that, once in awhile, we don't get a break in
life.''
