<HEAD>Senate Approves Monument To Women Who Served In Vietnam</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Congress has given final approval to a measure
calling for a monument in the nation's capital to American women
who served in the Vietnam War.
   The bill approved on voice vote Wednesday by the Senate does not
specify the location of the memorial to the 10,000 American women
