<1ST_LINE>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     10-13 0432</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0444</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Wintry Weather in The East</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Wintry weather slapped the East today with snow in four states
and freezing temperatures that snapped records in four cities.
   Frost and freeze warnings were posted from the Ohio and
Tennessee valleys to the Appalachians, and scattered frost was
expected as far south as Georgia, Mississippi and Alabama.
   Snow showers fell in northeast Ohio, northwest Pennsylvania and
northern New York state. Scattered snow showers fell in sections of
Vermont.
   Temperatures were in the upper teens and 20s across the upper
Great Lakes region, and in the 20s from southeast Ohio to the
central Appalachians.
   In Marquette, Mich., two low-temperature records were set in a
matter of minutes. Just before midnight Wednesday, the mercury
plunged to 20 degrees, setting a record for the date that was 5
degrees below the old mark set in 1967. By early today, the
temperature dropped to 19 degrees, a record for Oct. 13. The
previous record was 22 degrees set in 1974.
   Temperature records for Oct. 13 were also set in Columbus, Ohio;
Green Bay, Wis.; and Greer, S.C.
   Today's forecast called for rain across much of the Pacific
Northwest, snow showers over northern New England and mostly sunny
skies in the rest of the nation.
   High temperatures were expected to be in the 50s or 60s over
much of the country east of the Mississippi River; the 40s from the
northern and eastern Great Lakes to central New England; the 30s in
Maine; the 70s and 80s in much of the nation West of the
Mississippi; the 60s from the Pacific Northwest to the central
Pacific Coast; and the mid-90s in southwest Arizona.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 18
degrees at Marquette, Mich., to 79 degrees at Blythe, Calif., and
Phoenix.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 47 fair; Boston 40 fair; Buffalo 35 fair;
Charleston, S.C. 50 fair; Cincinnati 30 fair; Cleveland 41 cloudy;
Detroit 33 partly cloudy; Miami 71 fair; New York 41 fair;
Philadelphia 37 fair; Pittsburgh 29 fair; Portland, Maine 35 partly
cloudy; Washington 40 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 50 fair; Chicago 35 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth
57 fair; Denver 57 partly cloudy; Des Moines 42 fair; Indianapolis
29 fair; Kansas City 48 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 35 fair;
Nashville 41 fair; New Orleans 61 fair; St. Louis 42 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 52 fair; Anchorage 32 fair; Las Vegas 67
fair; Los Angeles 62 partly cloudy; Phoenix 79 fair; Salt Lake City
51 fair; San Diego 64 cloudy; Seattle 57 foggy.
   _Canada: Montreal 36 cloudy; Toronto 34 partly cloudy.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
