<HEAD>Teachers' Walkout Ends in Michigan Town</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HARTLAND, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Teachers in this lower Michigan district
returned to work today after negotiators agreed on binding
arbitration to end a strike that affected 3,000 students.
   A state-appointed fact-finder is expected to issue a ruling to
settle the strike by the 150 teachers within 30 days, said Tom
Parmeter, spokesman for the Hartland Education Association, which
