<HEAD>Nieman-Marcus Recalls Wrap Ornament</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two gift-wrap ornaments used by retailer
Nieman-Marcus are being recalled because they could pose a hazard
for children, the Consumer Product Safety Commission announced
Thursday.
   Affected are fuzzy squeeking duck ornaments and wooden Hansel
and Gretel ornaments, used on packages gift-wrapped by the company
in 1987 and early 1988.
   The duck could present a choking hazard, while the Hansel and
Gretel contains more lead in its paint than allowed by law, the
commission said.
   Consumers who received the ornaments as part of a gift-wrapped
parcel should return them to the nearest Nieman-Marcus store for a
refund of the wrapping charge.
   Those needing more information can contact the safety commission
at 1-800-638-2772.
