<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--MTV Fire,0104</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Offices of MTV Damaged In Fire</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The offices of MTV and its Video Hits 1 division
were seriously damaged Thursday by a fire that blew out windows in
the 25-story midtown building that houses numerous show business
enterprises.
   The flames were confined to the 10th floor, but water and smoke
damage from the 2 a.m. fire extended to MTV offices on the eighth,
ninth and 11th floors, said a company vice president, Barry Kluger.
   The cable broadcaster's studios are elsewhere and programming
was not interrupted, said Kluger. The cause of the fire was under
investigation.
