Government-Legislative. At Hall's suggestion, thousands of
Dayton-area citizens took part in a 40-hour fast or made monetary
pledges to those who did, raising $307,000 for famine relief. Ms.
Roukema has been a leader in an effort to provide increased aid to
the hungry in Ethiopia.
   Dr. Ralph Waldo Cummings, Emeritus Professor of Soil Science,
North Carolina State University, Educator-Scientist. Cummings'
research has helped increase food production in India and other
developing countries.
   Jeff Bridges, actor and three-time Academy Award nominee,
Celebrity. He has served on ttive.
Accion is said to have assisted more than 200,000 persons
throughout the Americas.
   National Public Radio, whose news programs have featured
coverage of hunger problems, Media-Communications. NPR recently
broadcast a series on efforts to avert future famine in Ethiopia.
   General Foods Fund, Inc., a tax-exempt foundation supported
exclusively by General Foods Corp. The fund gives an annual award
of $200,000 to people devoted to ending hunger.
