<1ST_LINE>d a AM-BRF--KennedyExhibit     10-13 0172</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Kennedy Exhibit,0175</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Kennedy Assassination Exhibit To Open Next February</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A $1.5 million exhibit at the site of the
assassination of President John F. Kennedy will open next year on
Presidents Day, an official said.
   Fund-raising and construction is nearly complete and details of
the exhibit and historical display will be announced Nov. 22, the
25th anniversary of the assassination, said Lindalyn Adams,
chairwoman of the Dallas County Historical Foundation.
   The exhibit will be on the sixth floor of the Dallas County
Administration Building in downtown Dallas. The building was known
as the Texas Schoolbook Depository in 1963 when Kennedy was shot as
he rode in a motorcade just outside the building.
   The Warren Commission determined that Lee Harvey Oswald fired
the shots from the sixth floor of the building.
   Ms. Adams said patrons will enter the building through a new
ground-level visitors center and ride an elevator to the exhibit
featuring films, videos and information about Kennedy's life and
the 1960s. The display opens Feb. 20, 1989.
</TEXT>
