<TEXT>
   The unemployment rate in Britain was 8 percent in
September, down from 9.8 percent in the same month of 1987.
   An estimated 2,266,900 people were unemployed last month, less
than the 2,772,200 people who were out of work in September 1987,
the Department of Employment reported.
   It said the number of people unemployed last month was less than
the reported figure, which was swollen by a postal strike that
prevented people from notifying the department they had found work.
