<HEAD>Lead Attorney Drops Out Of Case; No Public Explanation</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WAUCHULA, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The lead attorney has withdrawn from the
case of a couple who claim in a $100 million lawsuit that their
healthy baby was deliberately switched for a sickly one at a
Florida hospital 10 years ago.
   Marvin Ellin, a Baltimore lawyer, pulled out of the high-profile
case Wednesday, just as the FBI in Tampa closed a monthlong
investigation, saying it found no evidence that federal kidnapping
laws were violated.
   Ellin and attorney LaVonna Vice didn't explain their decision to
withdraw, but said it was unrelated to the strength of the case.
