another baby shortly after birth in Hardee Memorial Hospital in
1978 and that records were altered to hide the switch. Arlena, the
child they raised, died in August after heart surgery.
   The Twiggs say they want their real daughter back and believe
she is a 9{-year-old Sarasota girl. They have asked a state judge
in Sarasota to order the girl to undergo a genetic test to
determine her parents. There has been no ruling.
   Arthur Ginsburg, a lawyer representing the Sarasota girl's
father, said he would investigate the Twiggs' fitness as parents
before allowing the girl to undergo tests.
