<HEAD>Bush Edging Dukakis in Louisiana, Poll Says</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BATON ROUGE, La. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Republican George Bush holds a narrow
edge over Democrat Michael Dukakis among Louisiana voters, but Dan
Quayle is seen as a weak link on the GOP ticket, according to a
poll by Mason-Dixon Opinion Research.
   The Republican ticket is supported by 47 percent of those
polled, compared to 43 percent for the Democratic ticket of Dukakis
and Lloyd Bentsen.
   However, if voters were casting ballots for president only,
Bush's lead would increase to 51 percent to 40 percent for Dukakis.
   Fifty-six percent of those questioned believed that Quayle is
not qualified to serve as president, while 73 percent felt that
Bentsen would be qualified to serve.
   The poll, taken for Gannett News Service and several Louisiana
television stations, was based on telephone interviews of 821
registered voters from Oct. 7-9. It had a margin of potential error
of 4 percent.
</TEXT>
