<HEAD>Former Ford Executive Rodney Markley Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rodney W. Markley Jr., former Ford Motor Co.
vice president for governmental relations, died Wednesday in
Cannes, France, the company announced here Thursday. He was 75.
   Markley, a Denver native, joined Ford in Washington in 1951 and
represented the company in its relations with the government for 27
years, an era marked by the rise of consumer and environmental
groups.
   He was a friend of presidents, notably Lyndon B. Johnson and
Gerald R. Ford.
   Before joining Ford he was a Washington-based executive of the
Aircraft Industries Association and previously had been a contract
termination manager with Douglas Aircraft Corp., Santa Monica,
Calif.
