<2ND_LINE>BC-Britain-Unemployment,0137</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>British Jobless Rate Falls to 8 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Unemployment in Britain fell to a seasonally
adjusted 8 percent of the workforce in September from a revised 8.1
percent in August, the government said Thursday.
   The figure was down from 9.8 percent in September 1987.
   The Department of Employment previously reported August's
unemployment rate as 8 percent.
   Total seasonally adjusted unemployment was estimated at 2.266
million people in September, down from a revised 2.272 million in
August and 2.772 million in September 1987.
   The department said that last month's figure was swollen by a
postal strike which prevented people from notifying the department
that they had found employment.
   The monthly trend remained the same with a fall of about 40,000
unemployed a month, it said.
</TEXT>
