compared with last week's 81,552 and last year's 79,582.
   Canadian automakers were to build 17,036 cars this week, down
from 20,471 a week ago and up from last year's 15,292.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 18,002,
compared with 18,989 a week ago and 15,052 in the same week last
year.
